# ADR-002: Provider Abstraction Layer

Status: Accepted

Date: 2026-06-02

Decision Makers:
AgentForge Architecture Board

---

# Context

AgentForge is designed to support multiple model providers.

Supported Providers:

Cloud

- OpenAI
- Anthropic
- Gemini
- OpenRouter
- Azure OpenAI

Local

- Ollama
- LM Studio
- vLLM
- OpenAI-Compatible APIs

A decision is required regarding how the Runtime communicates with model providers.

---

# Problem

Should the Runtime communicate directly with each provider?

Example:

Runtime
↓
OpenAI

Runtime
↓
Anthropic

Runtime
↓
Ollama

Or should a Provider Abstraction Layer be introduced?

---

# Options Considered

## Option A — Direct Provider Integration

Architecture

Runtime
↓
OpenAI

Runtime
↓
Anthropic

Runtime
↓
Gemini

Advantages

Simple initially

Fast implementation

Disadvantages

Strong coupling

Difficult maintenance

Provider-specific logic leaks into runtime

Adding new providers becomes expensive

Decision

Rejected

---

## Option B — Provider Abstraction Layer

Architecture

Runtime
↓
Provider Manager
↓
Base Provider
↓
Provider Implementation

Advantages

Loose coupling

Provider independence

Extensibility

Cleaner architecture

Supports local models

Supports future providers

Disadvantages

Additional abstraction layer

Slightly more initial design effort

Decision

Accepted

---

# Decision

AgentForge will implement a Provider Abstraction Layer.

The Runtime must communicate only through:

BaseProvider

ProviderManager

The Runtime must never directly communicate with:

OpenAI SDK

Anthropic SDK

Gemini SDK

Ollama APIs

vLLM APIs

---

# Architecture

Runtime
↓
ProviderManager
↓
BaseProvider
↓
Provider Implementation

Examples

OpenAIProvider

AnthropicProvider

GeminiProvider

OpenRouterProvider

OllamaProvider

LMStudioProvider

vLLMProvider

---

# Base Provider Contract

All providers must implement:

connect()

generate()

stream()

count_tokens()

health_check()

---

Future Support

embeddings()

structured_output()

vision()

audio()

---

# Standard Request Model

Runtime communicates using:

ProviderRequest

Fields

messages

system_prompt

tools

temperature

max_tokens

metadata

---

Provider implementations translate to vendor-specific formats.

---

# Standard Response Model

Runtime receives:

ProviderResponse

Fields

content

tool_calls

usage

finish_reason

provider

model

latency

---

Runtime never receives provider-specific objects.

---

