# Local LLM Considerations

AgentForge has a strategic requirement:

Local LLM support must be a first-class capability.

Supported:

Ollama

LM Studio

vLLM

Private OpenAI-Compatible APIs

Provider Abstraction enables this without modifying runtime code.

---

# Future LLM Gateway

Future Architecture

Runtime
↓
ProviderManager
↓
LLM Gateway
↓
Providers

Responsibilities

Model Routing

Fallbacks

Cost Optimization

Governance

The Provider Abstraction Layer enables future gateway adoption.

---

# Consequences

Positive

✓ Provider Independence

✓ Cleaner Runtime

✓ Easier Testing

✓ Easier Maintenance

✓ Local LLM Support

✓ Future Gateway Support

---

Negative

✗ Additional Abstraction

✗ Slightly More Initial Complexity

---

# Enforcement

The Runtime Layer must never import provider-specific SDKs.

Allowed:

ProviderManager

BaseProvider

Provider Models

---

Forbidden:

import openai

import anthropic

inside Runtime modules.

Provider-specific code belongs only inside:

infrastructure/providers/

